Integration Procedure Invocation

You can invoke Integration Procedures from other OmniStudio tools such as OmniScripts and Cards. You can also invoke Integration Procedures from Apex classes, batch jobs, REST APIs, or Salesforce flows.

There are four ways to invoke an Integration Procedure:
1. From Apex: using the IntegrationProcedureService class
2. Unit Testing from Apex: setting up a test class in Apex to call and test an Integration Procedure
3. From REST APIs: using either a GET or POST call to run an Integration Procedure and retrieve the result
4. From Salesforce Flow: creating a Salesforce Flow component by defining a class with the @InvocableMethod annotation

The Vlocity batch framework also lets you run an Integration Procedure on a schedule, sending its input to an Integration Procedure or Apex method that processes the records.
title: Invoking OmniStudio Integration Procedures
